<P>There followed a cruise to Mexico where Orietta spent most of her time eating 
and managed to gain 4lb in a long weekend…… all for the sake of the little ones 
of course!!!! For Christmas we are off to Costa Rica for two weeks of sea, sun 
and volcanoes, after which Orietta will be ‘grounded’ but Michael is allowed to 
go skiing. </P>
<P>Christmas really has got us by surprise this year. The weather here in 
Houston is still warm and we tend to keep away from the commerciality of the 
shopping centres, as a result of which we have done no shopping, no card sending 
and no home decorating! Actually is has been extremely liberating being so 
disorganized. </P>
<P>We really would like to thank Paul &amp; Nicky here for their fabulous Christmas 
present to us all. We know from experience how much time and care it takes to 
put something like this together and are excited and grateful of the way it will 
make it SO much easier to keep in touch. One of the great downsides of being so 
far away from the clan is the fact that we miss seeing the little ones growing 
up and this will go some way to make up for it. Our hearts, thoughts and prayers 
are with you all this Christmas. We wish you happiness, health and prosperity 
for the new year…………… and keep the news coming!!!!!! </P>
